{"ts":"2026-06-27T14:08:59.033Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Implementing Authentication Logic**\n\nI'm making good progress! I've pinpointed the `handleAuthenticate` function to replace, covering lines 224-240. Now, I'm ready to insert the REST API authentication code directly into that segment. I'll get that set up next!\n\n\n**Refining Authentication Flow**\n\nI've replaced the existing logic with a new `handleAuthenticate` function. I've introduced a simulated scanning step using timeouts and state updates, giving the illusion of activity.  I've also added telemetry logging to record the cryptographic handshake initiation. I'm focusing on integrating the REST API call now, including error handling and the subsequent redirection based on role.\n\n\n**Integrating API Responses**\n\nI've integrated the REST API call into the authentication process. I'm focusing on handling both successful and unsuccessful responses. Upon a successful login, I'm fetching user information using the access token, but am temporarily storing the token in local storage (for MVP) while I set up better, more secure session storage and cookie handling. Telemetry logging is updated to reflect this handshake, as well as token storage.\n\n\n**Finalizing Role-Based Redirects**\n\nI've completed integrating role-based redirection. Based on the user's role obtained from the API response and enclave identity verification, I now push to the correct route after storing the session information. I've also incorporated a final telemetry log to indicate this last step, and I'm very nearly done with the authentication flow!\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T14:08:59.038Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"wg77e68l","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/components/portal/SecureLogin.tsx","old_text":"  const handleAuthenticate = async () => {\n    setScanning(true);\n    setScanStep(0);\n    \n    const stepIntervals = [250, 300, 350, 400];\n    for (let i = 0; i < stepIntervals.length; i++) {\n      await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, stepIntervals[i]));\n      setScanStep(prev => prev + 1);\n    }\n    \n    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 400));\n    setScanning(false);\n    setPreviewSession(selectedRole);\n    \n    const isGffStaff = !selectedRole.startsWith(\"client_\");\n    router.push(isGffStaff ? \"/admin/dashboard\" : \"/portal/dashboard\");\n  };","new_text":"  const handleAuthenticate = async () => {\n    setScanning(true);\n    setScanStep(0);\n    setError(\"\");\n    \n    const stepIntervals = [200, 250, 300, 350];\n    for (let i = 0; i < stepIntervals.length; i++) {\n      await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, stepIntervals[i]));\n      setScanStep(prev => prev + 1);\n    }\n    \n    logTelemetry(`[AUTH] Initiating cryptographic handshake with REST API for ${email}...`);\n\n    try {\n      const res = await fetch(\"/api/v1/auth/login\", {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n        body: JSON.stringify({ email: email.trim(), password }),\n      });\n\n      if (res.ok) {\n        const data = await res.json();\n        if (data.success && data.accessToken) {\n          logTelemetry(\"[AUTH] JWT token handshake complete. Verifying current enclave profile...\");\n          \n          // Store access token in localStorage for MVP dev only\n          // TODO: Production hardening - Use httpOnly cookies or secure session storage rather than localStorage to prevent XSS leakage of JWT tokens.\n          localStorage.setItem(\"gff_ai_access_token\", data.accessToken);\n\n          // Fetch user info using /api/v1/auth/me\n          const meRes = await fetch(\"/api/v1/auth/me\", {\n            headers: { \n              \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${data.accessToken}`,\n              \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n            }\n          });\n\n          if (meRes.ok) {\n            const meData = await meRes.json();\n            if (meData.success && meData.user) {\n              const u = meData.user;\n              logTelemetry(`[AUTH] Enclave identity verified: ${u.name} (${u.role.toUpperCase()})`);\n\n              // Store session in localStorage under key gff_ai_preview_session_v1\n              const sessionObj = {\n                name: u.name,\n                email: u.email,\n                role: u.role as any,\n                clearance: u.clearance || \"CLEARANCE LEVEL III (SANDBOX OPERATOR)\",\n                isMock: false,\n                label: `REST-API AUTH: ${u.clientAssociation || \"Core\"}`\n              };\n              localStorage.setItem(\"gff_ai_preview_session_v1\", JSON.stringify(sessionObj));\n              \n              // Dispatch change event to notify other components\n              window.dispatchEvent(new Event(\"gff_preview_session_changed\"));\n\n              await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 400));\n              setScanning(false);\n\n              // Redirect based on role\n              const isGffStaff = !u.role.startsWith(\"client_\");\n              router.push(isGffStaff ? \"/admin/dashboard\" : \"/portal/dashboard\");\n              return;\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      } else {\n        const errBody = await res.json().catch(() => null);\n        if (errBody && errBody.message) {\n          setError(errBody.message);\n          logTelemetry(`[ERROR] Verification rejected: ${errBody.message}`);\n          setScanning(false);\n          return;\n        }\n      }\n    } catch (err) {\n      logTelemetry(\"[SYS] API gateway unreachable. Activating cryptographic preview fallback...\");\n    }\n\n    // --- PRESERVE ROLE PREVIEW FALLBACK ---\n    logTelemetry(`[FALLBACK] Initializing dev preview session for ${selectedRole} [DEV FALLBACK]`);\n    setPreviewSession(selectedRole);\n    \n    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 400));\n    setScanning(false);\n\n    const isGffStaff = !selectedRole.startsWith(\"client_\");\n    router.push(isGffStaff ? \"/admin/dashboard\" : \"/portal/dashboard\");\n  };"}}}
