{"ts":"2026-06-27T14:11:10.069Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Celebrating Perfect Results!**\n\nI'm thrilled! The verification suite completed with a perfect score – all 25 test cases passed without a single failure! This confirms the codebase is robust and my changes integrated flawlessly, with no unexpected side effects. What a relief!\n\n\n**Analyzing Implementation Against Plan**\n\nI've just finished a code sanity check to ensure the implementation aligns perfectly with the requirements. All specified tasks are complete: the login routes are connected, the landing page is untouched, and AI tools are untouched. The Phase 4 local preview login now correctly authenticates against the specified backend endpoint, with token storage in `localStorage` including a crucial TODO for future production security. Finally, `/api/v1/auth/me` is called to load the current user after successful auth.\n\n\n**Verifying Dev Fallback System**\n\nI've implemented a robust dev fallback system, running a local preview if the API server is unavailable. A \"DEV FALLBACK ACTIVE\" badge clearly indicates this state, with telemetry logging. The sign-out feature now clears both the session and access token, redirecting to the login page. I've also verified the absence of production cookies and that the lint/build checks are passing. Finally, the status indicator is responsive.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T14:11:10.074Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"v1huk6j8","input":{"summary":"Successfully integrated the login UI with the MVP backend authentication endpoints.\n\n### Summary of Changes:\n1. **Credentials Pre-population Mapping**: Mapped mock roles on the login page to the actual API backend mock users (e.g. `s.vance@governance.gff.ai` for `gff_admin`, `a.mercer@apex-sovereign.gff.ai` for `client_admin`, and `s.jenkins@fed-treasury.gff.ai` for `client_member`). On role selection, the actual credentials are prefilled in the inputs to facilitate testing.\n2. **Active Mode Self-Test**: Added a `useEffect` self-test on mount to ping the `/api/v1/auth/login` endpoint. It dynamically sets `apiConnected` and displays a premium status badge: \"API SECURE ONLINE\" (green) when backend is active, or \"DEV FALLBACK ACTIVE\" (amber) when offline.\n3. **API-Driven Authentication**: Updated `handleAuthenticate` to POST to `/api/v1/auth/login`. On success, it stores the access token in `localStorage` as requested, adds a production security hardening `TODO` comment, and loads the active user using `/api/v1/auth/me`. The fetched user session is seamlessly structured and saved under the standard layout session key so all subpages and guards automatically display the real authenticated user.\n4. **Resilient Dev Fallback**: Preserved the Phase 4 local preview session as a fallback in case the API connection fails, clearly notifying the user with `[DEV FALLBACK]` logs in the console.\n5. **Secure Sign-Out**: Appended `localStorage.removeItem(\"gff_ai_access_token\")` to `clearPreviewSession` in `lib/preview-auth.ts`. This ensures that logging out completely clears both the portal session and the JWT access token, redirecting the user to `/portal/login` as required.\n6. **Robust Validation**: Verified compiling via `tsc --noEmit` (passed with 0 errors), ran full-codebase directory `eslint` (passed with 0 errors), and executed `verify-tools` deterministic test suite (passed 25/25 test cases successfully).","verified":true}}}
